$ ?

`?` evaluates expressions., `??` evaluates a C++ expression.

Symbols that occur in the expression are evaluated in the context of the current thread and process.

{ Print values of registers

  With MASM evaluation, the value of a → development/languages/assembler/x86/registers[register] can be printed simply like so:
code {
? rcx
code }
 
  With C++ evaulation, the name of the register needs to be prefixed with an at sign (`@`):
code {
?? @rcx
code }

  Compare with the → Windows/development/Debugging/tools/commands/r[`r` command].

}

sa:
  The → Windows/development/Debugging/tools/commands/dot/formats[`.formats`] command also evaluates expressions.
